 and the practices of migrants and the institutional actors they encounter.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Emigration & Immigration.2bisacsh1 aBernhard, Judith K., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBhuyan, Rupaleem, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBrasch, Katherine, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFortier, Craig, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGoldring, Luin, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHennebry, Jenna, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKisoon, Priya, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLandolt, Patricia , eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aLandolt, Patricia, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLi, Alan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMcLaughlin, Janet, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aNakache, Delphine, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSaad, Samia, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aValiani, Salimah, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aVillegas, Francisco, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aVillegas, Paloma E., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWright, Cynthia, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aYoung, Julie, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Toronto Press eBook-Package Backlist 2000-2013z978311049095440uhttps://doi.org/10.3138/9781442